   308	## 6. Reference-impl behavior (verification)
   309	
   310	The reference impl's `Store.integrate_trial` lives at
   311	[`reference/packages/eden-storage/src/eden_storage/_base.py`](../../reference/packages/eden-storage/src/eden_storage/_base.py)
   312	(method `integrate_trial`). It is a single composite-commit (chapter 05
   313	§2.2) that:
   314	
   315	1. Validates `trial.status == "success"`; otherwise raises
   316	   `InvalidPrecondition` (mapped to 409 `eden://error/invalid-precondition`
   317	   at the wire layer per chapter 7 §5/§7).
   318	2. Validates same-value idempotency: if `trial.trial_commit_sha`
   319	   equals the request body's `trial_commit_sha`, returns no-op (no
   320	   second write, no second event).
   321	3. Validates no-overwrite: if `trial.trial_commit_sha` is set and
   322	   differs from the request body's value, raises `InvalidPrecondition`.
   323	4. On success, writes the new `trial_commit_sha` field and emits
   324	   `trial.integrated` in one transaction.
   325	
   326	The reference impl does **not** inspect `trial.commit_sha` at integrate
   327	time; the §2(b) precondition is enforced transitively by the trial-
   328	status lifecycle (a trial cannot reach `success` without `commit_sha`
   329	set; see chunk-11c hardening of `drive_to_starting_trial` /
   330	`drive_to_success_trial`).
   331	
   332	The new tests are **not expected to fail** against the reference impl;
   333	they extend coverage of cross-artifact consistency (already enforced
   334	by the composite-commit primitive) and broaden status-precondition
   335	coverage to `error` and `eval_error` (which the existing
   336	`Store.integrate_trial` rejects via the same `status != "success"`
   337	branch as the existing v1 `starting` test). If any new test reveals
   338	a gap, it will surface at run time and the resolution is one of:
   339	amend the spec, fix the impl, fix the suite (per chapter 9 §7 — the
   340	reference impl does not have authority to reinterpret the spec).
   341	
   342	## 7. Test-design notes
   343	
   344	### 7.1 Cross-artifact-consistency tests are stronger than per-artifact tests
   345	
   346	The chunk's central new content is the **cross-artifact consistency**
   347	assertion: it's not enough to verify "field is set" and "event was
   348	emitted" independently; the new tests assert that they reference the
   349	**same** SHA. A bug where the composite-commit writes the field but
   350	emits the event with a stale SHA (or vice versa) would not be caught
   351	by the existing v1 tests; it would be caught by the new tests.
   352	
   353	This is also the right shape because it's **wire-observable** — a
   354	client that reads the field and the event sees the same value.
   355	
   356	### 7.2 Helper hardening discipline (per chunk-11c codification)
   357	
   358	`drive_to_error_trial` and `drive_to_eval_error_trial` MUST verify
   359	their own postconditions before returning. Specifically:
   360	

